<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">725.3211/46½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">26 April, 1915</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: My advice in this case
                            is, that first of all you talk with Mr. Naón and get from your talk with
                            him an intimation as to what is involved and how to handle the
                            matter.</p>
                        <p>Are you fully convinced that there is nothing in the proposed arrangement
                            among the A. B. C. that will stand in the way of or embarrass our own
                            American plan?</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>